<TITLE> RAB round up 6 'HuJI fugitives' in Dhaka, Feni, Ctg </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, August 1 (bdnews24.com)  Rapid Action Battalion arrested two suspected leaders of banned militant outfit Harkat-ul-Jihad-al Islami in the heart of the capital, and another four in southern districts, on Saturday. The Dhaka arrest was made by a team of RAB's detective wing at Nababerbagh in Mirpur-1, RAB deputy director Major Md Shakhawat Hossain told bdnews24.com. The two suspects were Mohammad Abdul Khair, 40, from Manikganj and Maulana Mohammad Musa, 38, from Chandpur, said Shakhawat. "A drive is on, we expect more such arrests," he said after the arrests. RAB later arrested four more HuJI operatives in Feni and Chittagong districts on information from Khair and Munna, being held in Dhaka. The latter four were identified by RAB as Abdul Aziz, 45, and Rezaul Karim, 40, Ansar Uddin Javed, 38, and Abdullah Al Hossain, 40. Of them Aziz was arrested from Feni and the others from Chittagong. Law enforcers arrested 41 HuJI operatives in Ukhiya, Cox's Bazar, in a single operation in 1996, said another RAB officer. "They later received bail and have been fugitive since" "The men arrested Saturday are among those originally arrested in 1996," said the officer, not wishing to be named. b
